This paper deals with sequence prediction models and their training algorithms, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses various learning algorithms and their properties. The second likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper focuses on sequence generation tasks such as machine translation and text summarization. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with reinforcement learning and policy optimization. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper mentions neural network models for sequence prediction. The fifth likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for scheduled sequence model learning.
